# outreach-factory secrets
#
# Copy to ~/.outreach-factory/.env and fill in the secrets you use.
# This file holds single-string API keys / tokens ONLY. Do NOT commit your
# real .env. Anything already exported in your shell or CI environment wins
# over what is set here.
#
# Gmail OAuth is NOT here: it uses credential files under
# ~/.outreach-factory/credentials/ (see docs/OPTIONAL-FEATURES.md), created by
# `./bin/outreach-factory init`.

# Reoon email-verification API key (optional; enables Tier-2 verify in
# /research-prospect). Falls back to ~/.outreach-factory/credentials/reoon_api_key.txt.
# REOON_API_KEY=

# Resend transactional-email API key (optional; fallback sender to Gmail).
# RESEND_API_KEY=

# Pre-send suppression-check API secret (optional). Only needed if you set
# security.suppression_check_url in your config and pointed
# security.suppression_check_secret_env at an env var name. The example name
# below matches examples/scholarfeed/config.scholarfeed.example.yml.
# SCHOLARFEED_ADMIN_SECRET=
